    <text id="F3526T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Colonel James G. Elder appoints John Ault as chaplain of the 126th
                Pennsylvania.</p>
            </div1>

        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head> 
                    Headquarters, 126th Regt. Pa. Vols. 
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1862-11-23">Nov. 23, 1862</date>
                        <name type="place">Camp near Fredericksburg Va.</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute/>
                </opener>

                <p>At a meeting of the field officers and Company Commanders of the 126th Regt. Pa.
                    Vols, on duty with the regt, held at these headquarters on this date, the <hi
                        rend="underline">Rev. John Ault</hi>, of Loudon, in Franklin County,
                    Pennsylvania, having been nominated unanimously to me for appointment as <hi
                        rend="underline">Chaplain</hi> of the said regiment; I, James G. Elder,
                    Colonel Commanding the 126th Regt. Pa. Vols. do, by those present appoint him
                    the said Rev. <hi rend="underline">John Ault</hi>, of Loudon, in the said County
                    of Franklin, a regularly ordained minister of the German Reformed Church, to be
                        <hi rend="underline">Chaplain</hi> of the 126th Regt. Pa. Vols </p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>In witness whereof I have herewith set my hand.</salute>
                    <signed>James G. Elder Col.<lb/> Comdg 126 Regt. Pa. Vols</signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">Attest<lb/> John Stewart Adjutant</seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
